Module com.example.bank_teller
Package com.example.bank_teller

Class BankTellerController

java.lang.Object
com.example.bank_teller.BankTellerController
public class BankTellerController extends Object
A GUI class to process the transactions (opening or closing an account, depositing into or withdrawing from an existing account, or printing account details) entered by the user through the graphical user interface and outputs the results to the text area present in the GUI.
Author:
Maryam, Nabihah

      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • accTypeIsSelected

      boolean accTypeIsSelected(boolean isOCTab)
      check whether account type has been selected
      Parameters:
      isOCTab - (boolean) if user is on the open/close tab of the GUI or deposit/withdraw tab
      Returns:
      false if no account type had been selected, true otherwise

    • applyInterestAndFees

      void applyInterestAndFees(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for Apply Interest and Fees button. Subtracts the fee and monthly interest from every account in the database and then prints updated balances of accounts with account information (by calling accountList from AccountDatabase) to text area in Account Database tab in GUI.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • calculateInterestandFees

      void calculateInterestandFees(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for Calculate Interest and Fees button. Calls accountsWithFeeAndInterest method in Account Database which returns String of all accounts with their fees and monthly interest and prints it to text area in Account Database tab in GUI.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • printAccounts

      void printAccounts(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for Print All Accounts button. Calls accountsList method in AccountDatabase to get list of all accounts as a String and prints it to text area in Account Database tab in GUI.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • printByAccountType

      void printByAccountType(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for Print All Accounts Sorted by Type button. Calls accountsByAccountType method in AccountDatabase to get list of all accounts, sorted by type as a String and prints it to text area in Account Database tab in GUI.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • open

      void open(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event handler for open button. This method calls the openHelper method to open an account.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • openHelperMethod

      void openHelperMethod(Account account)
      opens an account if account holder doesn't have an account of the same type in the database and all valid information is passed. this method can also reopen an existing closed account
      Parameters:
      account - (Account) containing information about account holder and initial balance

    • close

      void close(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for close button. This method calls close from AccountDatabase to close an account (if exists and hasn't been closed already).
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • deposit

      void deposit(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for deposit method. This method calls deposit in AccountDatabase and deposits money into an (open) existing account in the databse, if the amount is valid.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • withdraw

      void withdraw(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      Event Handler for withdraw button. This method calls withdraw in AccountDatabase and withdraws money from an (open) existing account in database if amount is valid and enough money exists with the account.
      Parameters:
      event - an Event representing some type of action

    • clearText

      private void clearText()
      clears all the components in open/close and deposit/withdraw tabs in GUI once an event occurs/button is pressed.

    • toIntCampusCode

      private int toIntCampusCode(String code)
      converts a string specifying campus to equivalent integer (campus code)
      Parameters:
      code - (String) campus name
      Returns:
      (int) campus code; 1 for New Brunswick, 2 for Newark, 3 for Camden

    • createAccount

      public Account createAccount(String command, Profile profile, double balance)
      creates an instance of Account (checking, savings, money market, or college checking) depending on what command user inputs
      Parameters:
      command - (String) can be O/C/D/W for open/close/deposit/withdraw respectively
      profile - (Profile) specifying details of account holder
      balance - (double) specifying initial balance in account being created
      Returns:
      an instance of Account
